cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses privacy-preserving query-based systems and attacks on them, which are topics that fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper specifically focuses on the effectiveness of Diffix, a query-based mechanism, in preventing inference of private attributes, which is a topic that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
